Brav Ghede Nibo is a rada spirit,http://books.google.com.au/books?id=mb6SDKfWftYC&pg=PA963&lpg=PA963&dq=is+Ghede+Nibo+rada&source=bl&ots=gY8qUULrmZ&sig=q29Ir8R5HTu9FbMbTX9c6QeZ9Is&hl=en&sa=X&ei=UtxzT9SzG6euiQeOgYnkDw&ved=0CEMQ6AEwBQ#v=onepage&q=is%20Ghede%20Nibo%20rada&f=false Google books: Encyclopedia of the African Diaspora ed Carole Boyce Davies considered a great healer. He is seen carrying a bottle of white rum infused with medicinal herbs. Often he also carries a staff and smokes a cigar.  Nibo is the special patron of those who die young, and as such is often conflated with the Catholic saint Gerard Majella. He is a psychopomp, an intermediary between the living and the dead. He gives voice to the dead spirits that have not been reclaimed from \below the waters\"."